methods.name: getPrecedence
methods.comment:
Get a precedence value for the specified variable.
 This value can be used to assist with LocalVariable.compareTo(Variable var)

methods.name: storageMatches
methods.comment:
Compare storage varnodes for two lists of variables.  No check is done to ensure that
 storage is considered good/valid (i.e., BAD_STORAGE, UNASSIGNED_STORAGE and VOID_STORAGE
 all have an empty varnode list and would be considered a match)

return.comment: true if the exact sequence of variable storage varnodes matches across two lists of variables.

methods.name: storageMatches
methods.comment:
Compare storage varnodes for two lists of variables.  No check is done to ensure that
 storage is considered good/valid (i.e., BAD_STORAGE, UNASSIGNED_STORAGE and VOID_STORAGE
 all have an empty varnode list and would be considered a match)

return.comment: true if the exact sequence of variable storage varnodes matches across two lists of variables.

methods.name: compare
methods.comment: Compare two variables without using the instance specific compareTo method.

return.comment:
a negative value if v1  v2, 0 if equal, and
 positive if v1  v2

if specified and variable storage size does not match the data-type size

methods.name: checkDataType

params.name: dataType
params.comment: datatype to be checked or null to produce suitable Undefined type

params.name: voidOK
params.comment: true if the zero-sized void data type is permitted

params.name: defaultSize
params.comment: datatype size to be used if specified datatype is null

params.name: program
params.comment: program which corresponds to this variable

methods.name: resizeStorage
methods.comment:
Perform resize variable storage to desired newSize.  This method has limited ability to grow
 storage if current storage does not have a stack component or if other space constraints
 are exceeded.

params.name: alignStack
params.comment: if false no attempt is made to align stack usage for big-endian

throws.comment: if unable to resize storage to specified size.

methods.name: checkVariableConflict
methods.comment: Check for variable storage conflict and optionally remove conflicting variables.

params.name: var
params.comment: existing function variable or null for new variable

params.name: newStorage
params.comment: new/updated variable storage

throws.comment: if deleteConflictingVariables is false and another variable conflicts

methods.name: checkVariableConflict
methods.comment: Check for variable storage conflict and optionally remove conflicting variables.

params.name: existingVariables

methods.name: getBaseStackParamOffset
methods.comment: Determine the minimum stack offset for parameters

return.comment: stack parameter offset or null if it could not be determined

methods.name: getThisParameter
methods.comment: Generate a suitable 'this' parameter for the specified function

return.comment:
this parameter or null of calling convention is not a 'thiscall'
 or some other error prevents it

methods.name: createPlaceholderClassStruct
methods.comment:
Create an empty placeholder class structure whose category is derived from 
 the function's class namespace.  NOTE: The structure will not be added to the data
 type manager.

params.name: classNamespace
params.comment: class namespace

params.name: dataTypeManager
params.comment: data type manager's whose data organization should be applied.

methods.name: findOrCreateClassStruct
methods.comment:
Find the structure data type which corresponds to the specified class namespace
 within the specified data type manager.  
 The preferred structure will utilize a namespace-based category path, however, 
 the match criteria can be fuzzy and relies primarily on the class name.
 While a new empty structure may be returned, it will not be added to the program's data type
 manager.

params.name: classNamespace
params.comment: class namespace

params.name: dataTypeManager
params.comment:
data type manager which should be searched and whose 
 data organization should be used.

return.comment: new or existing structure whose name matches the specified class namespace

methods.javadoc:
Find the structure data type which corresponds to the specified function's class namespace
 within the function's program.  One will be instantiated if not found.  
 The preferred structure will utilize a namespace-based category path, however, 
 the match criteria can be fuzzy and relies primarily on the class name.
@param function function's whose class namespace is the basis for the structure
@return new or existing structure whose name matches the function's class namespace or
 null if function not contained within a class namespace.
